✨WE’RE PREGNANT!!!✨

After 2 years of preparing….
11 months trying to conceive…
1 failed pregnancy….
8 AI treatments…
3 different donors…

We took a leap of faith together & our dreams are finally coming true. If you’ve been following us on social media since our first YouTube video in 2019, becoming moms together has been something we knew we wanted but wasn’t prepared for just yet. We talked about it, dreamed about it, cried together, became so impatient & started questioning so many things but it was all worth it in the end!! So thankful to have such a powerful bond with one another and to have chosen each other as our forever partner.

We want to thank all of you for supporting us in this journey, sending us luck, love and the best wishes! A special thanks to our donor family for making this possible and so easy-going for us! 🤍Another special thanks to @modernfertility for helping us start our journey from the very beginning! 

We can’t wait to add another Pisces to the DK family!! We’re so excited to meet you and become a family of 4! Also happy birthday to mommy Vee!!! ☺️🤞🏾🤰

Our pregnancy journey vlog will be uploaded tonight @ 12AM CST! Link in bio 🤍

Half-way there 👩🏾‍❤️‍💋‍👩🏾🤰🏾

We’re officially half way into our pregnancy journey and words cannot describe the moments we’ve shared these past few months!! So many tears of happiness and sadness. Cherishing these last few moments of us being a family of 3 (Cannot forget Julez ☺️🐩) has brought us even closer than before. We find out what you are in ONE week and boy are we excited!!! Cannot wait to purchase girl/boy clothes instead of straight gender neutral. Thank you everyone who has already started sending us things from our baby registry!! (link in bio) We’re so excited to start nesting already 🤣 but first we have to move into our new place. Things are moving quicker than we thought! ☺️ Baby DK is doing just fine, growing fast, healthy & extremely active!! You have given mommy hell in the beginning but she’s now starting to get her energy and groove back. We’re just so excited to meet this little soul we were gifted with! Counting down the days/months!! 🤞🏾🥹🤍

Creating your own reality of what a beautiful life means to you >>> 

I’ve really been enjoying this pregnancy and the changes that have came with it. Some days I feel like a superwoman and some days I feel so useless and weak, but that is okay. I am growing a whole human with a beautiful soul and this happens to be the beauty of this transforming chapter. I’ve faced a lot of reality checks and gained SO MUCH WISDOM, that I’m so thankful to be able to comprehend and cope with. I am so so so proud of myself. 

Decided to get away from the city and spend more alone time together before bringing in our baby girl in less than 6 months. I still can’t believe we are growing a family together & beating the odds 🥹🥹 These past few months have been so….bittersweet but I would say I was blessed with the most amazing support system to keep me going. I would also say I would do it all over again but…..the way first trimester did me, it’s Kristany turn next! 🤣🤍 XOXOX

ONE OF ONE 🪩✨👩‍👩‍👧

If you watch our Youtube channel, you know this was Kristany’s birthday gift, so she waited a LONG time to see @beyonce !!! She was awe the ENTIRE time 🤣☺️☺️

We both had the best time ever!!😭 Even Saige was jumping in the belly during the concert and this was our first time seeing her so active!! This night was a core memory for sure! 🥹🤍

It’s been about two months since we’ve been to the grocery store and purchased our fruits & vegetables. And lately, it’s been on our mind to feed the baby the freshest, most organic & healthiest foods possible (which is rare in America). Ever since we’ve been going to the farmer’s market, we haven’t looked back! The way our body communicates to us differently now than it did before is the reason why we’re advocating for home-grown fruits for life 😩 Did I mention the best way to save some $$? One of my followers recommended going to the farm for our meat so we’re excited to try that next! ✨

You + me = 3 👩‍👩‍👧🩷

Can’t believe time is flying so fast!!! Less than 4 months til we meet our little bean! ☺️🤍

Day 1/4 of our babymoon 🥹🩷

Really soaking in these moments with one another and also counting down the days til our family is complete. 🥹 Lots of people have been asking us, what is a “babymoon”? It’s basically a honeymoon but before baby get’s here! Like your last trip alone with just the two of you😊 

Arizona is AMAZING!!! We have been wanting to move out of Texas for a while now and been having a hard time deciding where 😩 Arizona is looking like #1 on our list! So peaceful and have a vintage feel which is right up our alley!! 
*swipe to see the self-driving Uber 😭😭*

Day 2/4 of our Babymoon 🤍

We went to go try some seafood from a place called Krazy Krab. It was a seafood/hibachi spot and you got to add some things from hibachi to your seafood boil! Davesha had to try broccoli in hers since it was the #1 add-on & she hadn’t gotten her greens in for the day😂 Kristany tried their Krazy Spicy sauce in her’s and boy was it HOT! 10/10!!

We then went to go watch the sunset at the peak of a hill by Arizona Military Museum. The sunsets down here with the mountains are so beautiful!!

Lastly, we went to go check out Spin Art Nation for a date night experience. Check out our last reel to see our feedback and experience! 😊🫶🏾

Day 3/4 of our Babymoon 💖

We decided to make this day a “chill” day. We left the house once during the day to go shopping & came across the coolest wholesale Mexican candy store 😩 We are both HUGE fans of any Mexican food/candy!! We stocked up with snacks for the rest of the trip and plane ride home.🤣

We then chilled at home by pool for the rest of the day until our dinner reservations at @tocamadera . This was the best entertainment we had while eating at a high-end restaurant we’ve ever seen! The food was a 8/10 but the entertainment made up for it! 😊

Day 4/4 of our Babymoon 🌵👩‍👩‍👧

Davesha wanted to do some hiking at the famous Hole in Rock of Arizona, giving me a damn heart attack! 🤣 She likes to forget she’s pregnant and can’t be as adventurous as she normally is but we made it work! 🫶🏾
Next, we went to visit the Butterfly Museum in the Arizona Botanical Garden! This is our second time visiting a butterfly museum and this one lets you create little homes for the butterflies and you can adopt one!! So stinking cute! 

We then stopped by @aceofwingz_ for some FIRE wingz!!! The most unique flavors & everything was SO GOOD! The owner was there and let us try his upcoming Mac and cheese that he’s about to add to the menu and MAN 😩😩😩 10/10!!

Our last stop was this super cool bookstore/media store we came across @bookmansphoenix ! This bookstore was so organized and had cute decorated sections for all categories. They even had a music and gaming area 🥹 They ate Barnes & Noble UP!! 🤣🤣🤣 Kristany wanted to get Saige a nostalgic book, we both have read growing up, for her bookshelf & Davesha found a human design book she’s been looking EVERYWHERE for in Dallas. 😊

Thank you for making each milestone so special & being down for all of my adventurous shenanigans! I got what I prayed for when I met you!❤️

If you know me, you know when it comes to traveling, I need to have either the ocean or lotssss of nature. I love peaceful trips with a zen feel. Trips where you can plan as you go without too much thought. Being pregnant, Arizona was the most perfect location for a peaceful babymoon. We didn’t want to do the city life for this special moment considering we already live in the city. It was just enough for us to do, good food to try, and for me to not be exhausted or in pain after. Can’t wait to come back with all of my friends! Now we wait on our missing puzzle piece!🥹👩‍👩‍👧
